fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
In preadditive categories, finite products
and coproducts coincide as biproducts, called direct
sums and written \oplus . Moreover, if the direct sums x\oplus  x and
y\oplus  y exist and given x\overset {f, g}{\rightrightarrows } y, the sum f + g coincides with
the map    x\xrightarrow {\Delta _x}x\oplus  x\xrightarrow {f\oplus  g} y\oplus  y\xrightarrow {\nabla _y} y. 

Finally, the diagram 





